Late to the party here. Just to clarify - from my reading of

  https://github.com/mkj/dropbear/blob/483b427335bad9f55d3cd62b6781392832fedeb2/dropbear.8#L90

the keepalive option enables a keepalive message every 10 seconds, not that a client connection can be verified *within* 10 seconds. The client will be disconnected after 3 keepalive timeouts, so that'll be a 30 sec window of no traffic from the client, is that what you're expecting?

Also, it doesn't sound like the -I idle_timeout is what you're after here at all. Do we want (fully working, but idle) sessions to drop after 30 mins?
